    <div class="container">
        <h1>Exploring the Apple Store: Insights Through Data Analysis</h1>
        
        <p>In this project, I performed an exploratory data analysis (EDA) on Apple Store data to uncover trends and insights about apps, genres, ratings, and prices. By investigating this dataset, I aimed to reveal patterns that can help understand the dynamics of the App Store and what factors contribute to app success.</p>
        
        <h2>Unique Apps and Missing Values</h2>
        <p>To start, I checked how many unique apps are in the dataset and looked for any missing values. Ensuring the dataset's integrity is a crucial first step in any analysis, as missing or duplicate data can distort the results.</p>

        <h2>Apps Per Genre: What's Popular?</h2>
        <p>One of the most interesting aspects of app data is understanding which genres are the most popular. By grouping apps by their genre, I identified which categories dominate the App Store.</p>
        <div class="chart">
            <h3>Chart: Number of Apps per Genre</h3>
            <img src="genre_chart.png" alt="Bar chart showing the number of apps in each genre">
        </div>

        <h2>Ratings Overview: What Do Users Like?</h2>
        <p>Understanding user ratings can give a direct indication of app quality and popularity. By looking at the minimum, maximum, and average ratings, I could get a sense of the overall distribution of ratings in the store.</p>

        <h2>App Pricing: Free vs. Paid</h2>
        <p>Pricing is another key factor in an app's success. I categorized apps into "Paid" and "Free" groups to see how they differ in terms of user ratings.</p>
        <div class="chart">
            <h3>Chart: Free vs Paid Apps Rating Comparison</h3>
            <img src="paid_vs_free.png" alt="Comparison chart of ratings for free vs. paid apps">
        </div>

        <h2>Language Support and User Satisfaction</h2>
        <p>Does offering an app in more languages lead to higher user satisfaction? I grouped apps by the number of languages they support and calculated their average ratings. This revealed whether language availability has a significant effect on ratings.</p>
        <div class="chart">
            <h3>Chart: Ratings by Language Support</h3>
            <img src="language_support.png" alt="Bar chart showing correlation between language support and ratings">
        </div>

        <h2>App Descriptions and User Ratings</h2>
        <p>Is there a relationship between the length of an app’s description and its rating? Longer descriptions might provide more information, potentially resulting in higher ratings. I explored this by analyzing description length and its correlation with user satisfaction.</p>
        <div class="chart">
            <h3>Chart: Ratings by Description Length</h3>
            <img src="description_length.png" alt="Chart showing the relationship between description length and ratings">
        </div>

        <h2>Conclusion</h2>
        <p>Through these analyses, I’ve uncovered a variety of insights about what makes apps successful on the Apple Store. Understanding these factors can help developers optimize their apps to attract more users and improve user satisfaction.</p>
    </div>

